>What are some types of stories you want to see that don't show up very often?
>Species/themes/settings/whatever
Shamelessly reposting because I enjoy the potential story and world building discussion and not because I spent too much time typing all this on the tiny phone screen keyboard before checking if the thread's already at end.
>species
Felines or alien things resembling felines as companion (or should I say 'catpanion') species, smol woodland creatures as the main form of endemic sapient lifeforms and abstract forms of aquatic life as the blue and orange things floating in the aether that you may or may not even think about attempting contact with, with some form of ancient automatons thrown into the mix for a good measure.
>themes
"""Spess""" ship based travel, mecha based exploration and combat, logistics of operating in completely alien environs, first contact and/or re-establishing relations with long lost outposts/expeditions/civilisations, digging through remains/ruins/still functional automated complexes of ancient sufficiently technologically advanced species.
>settings
High sci-fantasy space opera, so whatever more or less artificial structures floating in the outer aether and alien worlds / dimensions. Maybe something like Spelljammer or Sunless Skies but with the non combat specific ships being kept mostly in the role of transportation devices while the mecha are used as the main muscle wherever applicable. Perhaps with some Monster Hunter (using various biomass fragments of felled fauna, harvested flora or other resource deposits in manufacturing parts / general maintenance of hardware) thrown into the mix.
>whatever
Graphic and visceral descriptions interspersed with bouts of technobabble welcome. Detailed petting sequences of fluffy waifur(s) also, if not more, welcome. Missy cameo mandatory.

So, discuss stories or whatever.
